.TH "snd_hdac_display_power" 9 "snd_hdac_display_power" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hdac_display_power \- Power up / down the power refcount
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" snd_hdac_display_power
.BI "(struct hdac_bus *bus "  ","
.BI "unsigned int idx "  ","
.BI "bool enable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
HDA core bus
.IP "idx" 12
HDA codec address, pass HDA_CODEC_IDX_CONTROLLER for controller
.IP "enable" 12
power up or down
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used by either HD-audio controller or codec driver that
needs the interaction with graphics driver.

This function updates the power status, and calls the \fBget_power\fP and
\fBput_power\fP ops accordingly, toggling the codec wakeup, too.
